be the one that deploys the contract. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.\",\"kind\":\"dev\",\"methods\":{\"constructor\":{\"details\":\"Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.\"},\"owner()\":{\"details\":\"Returns the address of the current owner.\"},\"renounceOwnership()\":{\"details\":\"Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.\"},\"transferOwnership(address)\":{\"details\":\"Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.\"}},\"version\":1},\"userdoc\":{\"kind\":\"user\",\"methods\":{},\"version\":1}},\"settings\":{\"compilationTarget\":{\"@openzeppelin/contracts/access/Ownable.sol\":\"Ownable\"},\"evmVersion\":\"osaka\",\"libraries\":{},\"metadata\":{\"appendCBOR\":false,\"bytecodeHash\":\"ipfs\"},\"optimizer\":{\"enabled\":true,\"runs\":200},\"remappings\":[],\"viaIR\":true},\"sources\":{\"@openzeppelin/contracts/access/Ownable.sol\":{\"keccak256\":\"0x9a6518f7abc4fc9be6dcc12254daafa0820b1390c3a32d80ebbb2e3aa0a03284\",\"license\":\"MIT\",\"urls\":[\"bzz-raw://e9abce554c3c4b00b762ca8da00c95051ef4f7a16bf0fc545794f78f8786a41f\",\"dweb:/ipfs/QmYWKJnAzcVb1Hf94WAFVQHuF4HVX6PfLnCtrKvd84ezSh\"]},\"@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Context.sol\":{\"keccak256\":\"0xd78f7b72d8cbab9d7c415bae78d0f586749bb697701819dabab69fd470ee017a\",\"license\":\"MIT\",\"urls\":[\"bzz-raw://3f53b4419269cdd4ac7bc16d69c2137ccd87c49fb35f2614cbfdfca5cbcf2e22\",\"dweb:/ipfs/QmZdfkYfHj7TBcBErGRggRqaSp22FEaEPJu1ysw8VvajZD\"]}},\"version\":1}"}},"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol":{"ERC20":{"evm":{